---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Masthead from '../components/Masthead.astro';
import SectionEyebrow from '../components/SectionEyebrow.astro';
---
<Base title="Colophon" description="A technical and editorial colophon for the website of the American Institute for Michaels.">
  <Masthead
    eyebrow="Colophon"
    title="On the making of this site."
    lede="A modest colophon is a courtesy. The Institute is pleased to record below the typefaces, tools, and conventions employed in the construction and continued maintenance of this website."
  />

  <section class="container section">
    <div class="prose">
      <SectionEyebrow index="I" label="Typography" />
      <p>
        The principal text of the Institute is set in <strong>Source Serif 4</strong>,
        designed by Frank Grießhammer for Adobe and released to the public
        under the SIL Open Font License. Source Serif is a transitional serif
        with restrained authority, well suited to the Institute's tone. The
        family is used here in Regular and Semibold weights.
      </p>
      <p>
        Subsidiary text — eyebrows, captions, navigation, the donor roll — is
        set in <strong>Inter</strong>, designed by Rasmus Andersson and likewise
        offered under the SIL OFL. Inter is used principally in Regular and
        Semibold; small caps and tabular figures are employed where the
        material warrants.
      </p>
      <p>
        Both faces are self-hosted via the Fontsource project. No connection
        to a third-party font CDN is established when this page is loaded.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule container" />

  <section class="container section">
    <div class="prose">
      <SectionEyebrow index="II" label="Construction" />
      <p>
        The site is a static document, hand-built using
        <a href="https://astro.build" rel="noopener">Astro</a> with strict
        TypeScript and a plain CSS token system. There is no framework
        beyond Astro itself; no client-side runtime is shipped except where a
        small piece of behavior (the fellowship form, the state lookup,
        forthcoming pages of comparable scope) plainly requires it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Images are processed at build time via Astro's image pipeline. WebP
        is the principal delivery format; a small number of decorative
        photographs receive the Institute's standard editorial grayscale
        treatment by way of CSS filter.
      </p>
      <p>
        The whole is hosted on GitHub Pages and served through Cloudflare's
        public DNS. Source code is available on request.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section">
    <div class="prose">
      <SectionEyebrow index="III" label="Editorial Conventions" />
      <p>
        The Institute follows a small number of standing editorial
        conventions, set out in full on the <a href="/style-guide">style guide
        page</a>. Briefly: <em>The Institute</em> takes a singular verb;
        numerals under one hundred are spelled out; the Oxford comma is used
        without exception; em dashes are flanked by hairline spaces.
      </p>
      <p>
        Citation style follows that of the <em>Quarterly Review of Civic
        Onomastics</em>, a publication for which the Institute holds no
        formal affiliation but whose conventions it has found congenial.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section">
    <div class="prose">
      <SectionEyebrow index="IV" label="Accessibility" />
      <p>
        The site is built to meet, at minimum, WCAG 2.1 AA. All images carry
        descriptive alternative text; navigation is keyboard-traversable; a
        skip link is provided at the head of every page. The Institute
        welcomes correspondence on accessibility matters, which may be
        addressed to <a href="mailto:hello@michaelinstitute.org">the general
        office</a> with the subject line "Accessibility."
      </p>
      <p>
        Reduced-motion preferences are respected throughout. Color contrast
        ratios were last audited in the third quarter of fiscal 2025.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section">
    <div class="prose">
      <SectionEyebrow index="V" label="Privacy" />
      <p>
        The Institute does not employ analytics scripts, third-party
        trackers, or advertising tags of any description. Page visits are
        not logged at the application layer; we have no record of which
        pages you have read.
      </p>
      <p>
        Form submissions on the fellowship and contact pages produce a
        client-side acknowledgment only; no data is transmitted to the
        Institute's servers without your further action.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section">
    <div class="prose">
      <SectionEyebrow index="VI" label="Acknowledgments" />
      <p>
        The Institute records its thanks to the open-source maintainers of
        the tools above; to the photographers of the editorial bands, whose
        images are licensed via the Unsplash Trust; and to the founding
        members, whose patient correspondence over the past five fiscal
        years has provided the material from which this site was assembled.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .section { padding-block: var(--s-6); }
  .prose strong { color: var(--brand-olive); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
